==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Crenature
<hw>Cren"a*ture</hw> <pr>(kr?n"?-t?r ⟦or⟧ kr?"n?-; 135)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A rounded tooth or
notch of a crenate leaf, or any part that is crenate; -- called also
<altname>crenelle</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The state of being crenated or notched.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crenel</ent>⟦br⟧
